Background and Analysis:
	 
The Faculty Association and the District reached tentative agreement and voting members of the Faculty Association have ratified the tentative agreement on the topic of 2015-2016 and 2016-2017 compensation. The Board is hereby requested to approve the 2015-2016 and 2016-2017 compensation settlement reached between the Foothill-De Anza Community College District and the Faculty Association. 
	 
Effective July 1, 2015:
A salary adjustment of 3.00% (equivalent to the State-provided 1.02% COLA plus additional 1.98%) on all salary schedules, Appendices A, B, B.1, C, C.1 , D, D.1, E, and G; 
An adjustment to Article 26 Summer Session increasing compensation from 70% to 74% of the full time salary schedule, Appendix A; 
An adjustment to Article 38 Professional Achievement Awards increasing the award amounts as follows:
Award #1 from $2000 to $3000;
Award #2 from $3000 to $3750, for a total of $6750;
Award #3 from $3750 to $4250, for a total of $11,000;
Award #4 from $3750 to $4500, for a total of $15,500; and
An adjustment to Article 36 Professional Conference Fund increasing the amount of the district's allocation by $50,000 from a total of $126,000 to $176,000 per year. Further, any remaining dollars, year to year, shall be rolled to the next year, up to a maximum of $25,000 per year. Conferences scheduled to be concluded in the 2015- 16 year, as well as summer 2016 conferences concluded prior to start of Fall quarter 2016, shall be paid from the 2015-16 base funds of $176,000. Any remaining dollars from 2015-16 shall roll over to the 2016-17 year, up to a maximum of $25,000.
Terms:  The salary adjustments to Appendices A, B, B.1, C, C.1, D, D.1, E, and G, Article 26 Summer Session, and Article 38 Professional Achievement Awards shall be retroactive to July 1, 2015. Such payments shall include payment for the entire portion of any assignment paid as a Summer Session 2015 assignment.  The adjustments and any retroactive pay shall commence as soon as possible following faculty ratification and approval by the Board itself, but not later than 60 days past ratification and approval, anticipated for the June 2016 pay period.
	 
Effective July 1, 2016:
A salary adjustment of 0.60% (equivalent to the State-anticipated 0.47% COLA per the Governor's preliminary budget plus additional 0.13%) on all salary schedules, Appendix A, B, B.1, C, C.1, D, D.1, E, and G;
In the event the state approved COLA is higher than 0.60%, the salary adjustment shall be equal to the state approved COLA;
In the event the district receives an additional augmentation to the base or additional funding for full-time faculty hiring, FA reserves the right to reopen negotiations regarding that funding;
An adjustment to Article 26 Summer Session increasing compensation from 74% to 76% of the full time salary schedule, Appendix A;
An adjustment to Article 36.2 Professional Conference Fund increasing the maximum amount per person per year from $1000 to $1600 as reimbursement for the cost of attendance by faculty employees at professional conferences or seminars, including the cost of fees, travel, lodging, and meals.
	 
Terms:  The salary adjustments to Appendices A, B, B.1, C, C.1, D, D.1, E, and G, shall be effective July 1, 2016.  Such payments shall include the entire portion of Summer Session 2016 assignments. Adjustments shall commence following faculty ratification and approval by the Board itself with payments anticipated for the July 2016 pay period.
	 
Attached are corresponding changes to the Agreement:  Appendix I (Application for Professional Achievement Award), MOU between Foothill-De Anza Community College District and the Foothill-De Anza Faculty Association, and related Articles as follows: Article 24 - Salaries for Faculty Employees, Article 26 -Summer Sessions, Article 36 - Professional Conference Fund, and Article 38 - Professional Achievement Awards.
	 
